There is a script "converter.sh" which
takes as input an LHE file and turns it into a ROOT file with the angles calculated and some other information.
>>> bash converter.sh <filename>.lhe

There is an example script plotPdfs_5D.C which plots the angles and PDF projections of those angles.  It assumes a PDF (not in CVS yet) for your signal that the user must provide.  


-- Check out the PDFs in the maintained CJLST area

cvs co -p UserCode/CJLST/ZZMatrixElement/MELA/src/RooSpinOne_7D.cc > PDFs/RooSpinOne_7D.cc
cvs co -p UserCode/CJLST/ZZMatrixElement/MELA/src/RooSpinOne_7D.h > PDFs/RooSpinOne_7D.h
cvs co -p UserCode/CJLST/ZZMatrixElement/MELA/src/RooSpinTwo_7D.cc > PDFs/RooSpinTwo_7D.cc
cvs co -p UserCode/CJLST/ZZMatrixElement/MELA/src/RooSpinTwo_7D.h > PDFs/RooSpinTwo_7D.h

-- Check out other PDFs not in CJLST
cvs co -p UserCode/Whitbeck/snowmass2013/src/RooSpinZero_7DComplex.cc  > PDFs/RooSpinZero_7DComplex.cc
cvs co -p UserCode/Whitbeck/snowmass2013/src/RooSpinZero_7DComplex.h  > PDFs/RooSpinZero_7DComplex.h
